Building on the previous chapters we introduce the concept of formatting Worksheets and managing a Workbook – for both on screen and printed presentation. While it may not be important to focus on the presentation and management of your Workbook when making trivial spreadsheets, it is critical to do so when you have external users to whom you present your work (e.g., a boss). It is also critical to pay attention to presentation when you work with a large amount of data. In this section, we will first practice the analytical skills we acquired last week, we will then turn our attention on formalizing the process of designing a good Workbook.

