## Exercise Overview

**Objective** Practice the use of basic and intermediate Excel functions. You will be working with a file that has 250 rows, with data about the top 250 restaurant chains in the US.

**Scenario** Cousin Anna liked your effort. She particularly commended your for thinking about separating out your results into a separate worksheet. You began to understand the importance of separating data, computations and presentations. However, she points out that you did not do a lot of important things that characterize a good Excel workbook, such as protecting the worksheet and formatting it for quality printing. Anna sent you a new file to work on, stating: *"I think that you are getting the hang of this. Here is a more meaningful and comprehensive dataset. Go at it!"*

